Step 1
Enzyme family expansions plot

You are now at the enzyme family internal database. At this stage enzymes families (columns), from central metabolic pathways (groups of columns separated by thick grey lines) from three model actinomycetes (S. coelicolor, M. tuberculosis, C. glutamicum) have been used as queries to identify their homologs in all the genomes in the DB. The table shows the number of homologs in each genome for each enzyme family. The lines were sorted following a species tree to allow for taxonomic resolution of the enzyme family expansion process.

Place the mouse pointer over a number in the table to get more information:

Pathway- -enzyme /Strain/ Gene Identifiers (GIs)

For each homolog found.

If a box in the table is red it means that the number of homologs for that enzyme family in that genome is expanded, suggesting the potential for the evolution of a new enzyme function perhaps in Natural Product biosynthesis, the next step allows to distinguish those cases.
